<L>__{12. weather deck night}
<A>__{the uppermost or weather deck consists of two parallel gangways linking the forecastle (forward) to the quarterdeck (aft). the lead is dropped from the bows. as pullings walks aft to the quarterdeck as each man lets go his coils of the deep sea line.}
<C>__{crewmen}
<D>__{watch there! watch}
<A>__{somewhere a bell sounds and the silent figures of the watch call from their stations.}
<C>__{watch captains}
<D>__{ lifebuoy all's well! starboard gangway all's well! starboard bow all's well!}
<A>__{over this, the splash of the lead and the repeated cry of "watch there! watch!"}
